From e4006ca18e8983c219c9524dfda7f09f261cd7ae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcos <marcosbrendonaz@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 02:07:14 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 11/13] refactor: remove auto-click, add bot-controlled
 Turnstile solve via WebSocket CDP

Remove hardcoded Turnstile auto-click (chameleon_autoclick.cc). Bots now
control everything via raw WebSocket CDP:
- Target.getTargets to find cross-process iframes
- Target.attachToTarget to connect to iframe process
- Page.createIsolatedWorld + Runtime.evaluate with pierce

This works cross-process without disabling site isolation. The pierce
in isolated world runs inside the iframe's own process.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
